<div class="container form-wide">
  <form action="/blog/update/<%= article.id %>" method="POST">
		<h1 class="form-heading">Edit Blog Article</h1>

		<% if(flash && flash.err) { %>
        <div class="alert alert-danger">
      <% Object.keys(flash.err).forEach(function(error) { %>
        <div><%- flash.err[error].message %></div>
      <% }) %>
      </div>
      <% } %>
		
		<div class="form-group article-title-field">
			<label for="articleTitle">Article Title</label>
			<input type="text" id="articleTitle" class="form-control" value="<%= article.title %>" name="articleTitle">
		</div>
    <div class="panel-group" id="accordion">
      <div class="panel panel-default">
        <div class="panel-heading">
          <h4 class="panel-title">
            <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseOne">
              To add an image(s) to an article they must first be uploaded to flickr. Click here for instructions on how to do that.
            </a>
          </h4>
        </div>
        <div id="collapseOne" class="panel-collapse collapse">
          <div class="panel-body">
            First, go to <a target="_blank" href="https://www.flickr.com">flickr.com</a> and log in using the credentials on <a target="_blank" href="https://docs.google.com/file/d/0BxMBcEWJ5pm9ZDZGOFRCT3Ntc2s/edit">this google doc</a> (don't have access to the google doc? <a target="_blank" href="mailto:astadke@gmail.com">let maintenance know</a>). Once logged in, click "Upload" and upload all the necessary images. To put an image in an article, click the image in the flickr photostream. Then, in the right-hand panel, click the share icon (box with arrow out of top-right corner). Here, click "HTML" and make sure the "HTML" radio button is also selected. In the embed code, highlight and copy ONLY the "src" URL, excluding the quotes. This should start with something like "https://farmX.staticflickr...." and end with the file extension. Last step: back on the blog edit page, insert an image using the CKEditor toolbar and paste this src URL into the URL field. That should do it!
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
		<div class="form-group">
			<label for="articleBody">Article Text:</label>
      <textarea class="form-control" id="articleBody" name="articleBody"><%= article.articleBody %></textarea>
		</div>
    <div class="form-group">
      <label class="radio-inline">
        <input type="radio" name="publish" value="live" checked> <% if(article.published){ %>Keep Published<% } else { %>Publish Now<% } %>
      </label>
      <label class="radio-inline">
        <input type="radio" name="publish" value="draft"> <% if(article.published){ %>Unpublish<% } else { %>Keep Saved as Draft<% } %>
      </label>
    </div>
		<div class="form-group col-md-2">
			<input type="submit" class="btn btn-lg btn-primary btn-block" value="Update Article"/>
		</div>
		<div class="form-group col-md-1 form-cancel-div">
			<a class="form-cancel" href="/blog/admin">Cancel</a>
		</div>
		<input type="hidden" name="_csrf" value="<%= _csrf %>" />
    <% if(!article.published){ %><input type="hidden" name="notAlreadyPub" value="true" /><% } %>
	</form>
</div>
<script src="/ckeditor/ckeditor.js"></script>
<script>
  // text editor
  CKEDITOR.replace('articleBody', {
    height: 400
  });
</script>